The cycling performance of the CQDs-PMIA sensor was examined, and the CQDs-PMIA sensor was tested five times in sequence using an acid/base buffer solution. The results are shown in Fig. 8
                        . The figure shows that the sensing performance of the CQDs-PMIA sensor remained stable after five cycles of testing in both fluorescence and colorimetric detection modes. This indicates that it has good cycling performance. To examine the practicality of the CQDs-PMIA sensor, the CQDs-PMIA sensor was used to detect the pH value of actual water samples. In the experiment, four water samples, rainwater, lake water, pure water, and phosphate buffer solution, were selected for evaluation, and the measured results were compared with a commercial electrochemical pH meter (Table 1
                        ). The results showed that both colorimetric and fluorescence detection modes exhibited good accuracy, and the CQDs-PMIA sensor yielded results comparable to those of commercial instruments. The above results show that the developed CQDs-PMIA sensor can be applied to the accurate measurement of pH in real samples and has promising applications.
